and get back to you, Mr. President.

248
00:18:59,389 --> 00:19:01,683
Thank you. Robert,
what's the latest on the omnibus?

249
00:19:01,767 --> 00:19:04,519
The legislation should go to
the floor in the next couple of months.

250
00:19:04,603 --> 00:19:05,771
The leadership is pushing...

251
00:19:27,126 --> 00:19:29,419
Set up calls with both
Lockheed and Northrop.

252
00:19:29,503 --> 00:19:32,172
We'll pay people to get trained
and call it a job.

253
00:19:32,255 --> 00:19:34,133
It isn't a job
unless the union says it is.

254
00:19:34,215 --> 00:19:37,803
Well, one step at a time. You set up
the training and I'll speak to the AFL.

255
00:19:37,886 --> 00:19:39,179
Are the AARP here?

256
00:19:39,262 --> 00:19:42,223
In the lobby. The chairman told me
they want to support Dunbar.

257
00:19:42,307 --> 00:19:43,642
They're just trying to rattle us.

258
00:19:43,725 --> 00:19:45,686
Dunbar is promising
to save Social Security.

259
00:19:45,769 --> 00:19:48,563
Go after Wall Street and government
waste instead of entitlements.

260
00:19:48,647 --> 00:19:49,648
Well, get them in here.

261
00:19:49,731 --> 00:19:52,609
You have your call list. Their meeting's
not for another ten minutes.

262
00:19:52,693 --> 00:19:55,904
Start bringing them over. It'll take them
that long to hobble over on their walkers.

263
00:19:55,988 --> 00:19:58,281
- Francis?
- I'll go get them.

264
00:19:58,365 --> 00:19:59,992
I only have a few minutes.

265
00:20:07,624 --> 00:20:10,377
You singled me out today on purpose.

266
00:20:10,460 --> 00:20:12,880
- What?
- The cabinet meeting.

267
00:20:12,963 --> 00:20:14,840
If I'm gonna invite you
to cabinet meetings,

268
00:20:14,923 --> 00:20:16,800
there's not gonna be any kid gloves.

269
00:20:16,884 --> 00:20:18,593
Don't make it sound like a favor.

270
00:20:18,677 --> 00:20:20,512
You wanted to be there. I agreed.

271
00:20:20,595 --> 00:20:23,015
Well, so I could be informed
and do my job.

272
00:20:23,098 --> 00:20:26,018
Everyone in that room is judged
by what they bring to the table.

273
00:20:26,101 --> 00:20:28,436
What you brought to the table
was amateurish.

274
00:20:29,437 --> 00:20:31,190
Both Cathy and I proposed that plan.

275
00:20:31,314 --> 00:20:34,151
I fault her as much as you.
You're making this too personal.

276
00:20:34,234 --> 00:20:38,072
It is personal. I think you're
punishing me for what happened in Russia.

277
00:20:38,155 --> 00:20:39,698
Oh, come on.

278
00:20:39,781 --> 00:20:42,826
Well, you said it on the plane.
Appointing me was a mistake.

279
00:20:42,910 --> 00:20:44,828
Yeah, you said far worse things to me.

280
00:20:44,912 --> 00:20:47,998
Yes, and I've gone out of my way
to put that fight behind us.

281
00:20:48,082 --> 00:20:50,000
Oh, really? Like with Thomas?

282
00:20:50,084 --> 00:20:51,919
When you screamed at us
for waking you up.

283
00:20:52,002 --> 00:20:54,129
- I didn't scream.
- It was embarrassing.

284
00:20:54,213 --> 00:20:55,589
Who cares what he thinks?

285
00:20:55,672 --> 00:20:57,841
He was our guest
and you walked in there like--

286
00:20:57,925 --> 00:21:00,052
I think you're searching for things
that aren't there

287
00:21:00,135 --> 00:21:03,138
and ignoring the things that are,
like this photograph flinching nonsense.

288
00:21:03,222 --> 00:21:04,806
Oh, Jesus.

289
00:21:07,017 --> 00:21:10,020
- Do you want me to resign, Francis?
- Don't be ridiculous.

290
00:21:10,104 --> 00:21:12,439
Just say it.

291
00:21:12,522 --> 00:21:14,691
You never wanted me to be ambassador.

292
00:21:14,775 --> 00:21:16,651
You remember what you
said to me on the plane?

293
00:21:16,735 --> 00:21:18,570
You should have never made me president.

294
00:21:18,653 --> 00:21:20,280
I was upset. I didn't mean it.

295
00:21:20,363 --> 00:21:22,532
You did mean it.
You think you made me.

296
00:21:22,616 --> 00:21:25,326
No, I don't.
I think we're a team, actually.

297
00:21:25,410 --> 00:21:27,412
Well, we're not a team at the moment.

298
00:21:32,500 --> 00:21:34,419
I can't believe we've become this.

299
00:21:35,879 --> 00:21:37,547
- Become what?
- Like everyone else.

300
00:21:42,219 --> 00:21:43,220
You ready, sir?

301
00:21:43,303 --> 00:21:45,430
No, just give me a minute.
Let the smoke clear.

302
00:22:10,831 --> 00:22:12,332
Where are we at?

303
00:22:41,653 --> 00:22:43,362
Her hair's different.

304
00:22:44,447 --> 00:22:45,991
But I--

305
00:22:47,242 --> 00:22:49,328
- Where was this taken?
- Santa Fe.

306
00:22:49,410 --> 00:22:51,538
I've narrowed the search
to focus just on that city.

307
00:22:51,621 --> 00:22:54,166
This is all I have,
but I think it's a good start.

308
00:22:55,374 --> 00:22:58,461
- I should go there.
- No. These photos are three weeks old.

309
00:22:58,545 --> 00:23:01,715
- She might have been passing through.
- Or she might still be there.

310
00:23:01,798 --> 00:23:05,093
Okay, but if you start asking questions,
you might tip her off.

311
00:23:05,177 --> 00:23:07,179
Get me more, then.

312
00:23:09,472 --> 00:23:11,099
How's my passport coming?

313
00:23:13,101 --> 00:23:16,146
I'll get the lock lifted
when you find her.

314
00:23:16,230 --> 00:23:18,982
I've shown you some progress.

315
00:23:19,066 --> 00:23:21,735
I think I should be seeing
progress on your side, too.

316
00:23:21,818 --> 00:23:22,777
This isn't enough.

317
00:23:22,861 --> 00:23:24,863
They just arrested
another one of my friends.

318
00:23:24,946 --> 00:23:27,406
- They could charge me at any minute.
- Gavin...

319
00:23:27,490 --> 00:23:30,827
The things that I've had to do
to get this much are fucked up.

320
00:23:30,911 --> 00:23:33,247
An exact location.

321
00:23:34,164 --> 00:23:35,332
That was our deal.

322
00:23:41,755 --> 00:23:43,590
Can you get me the camera feed?

323
00:23:43,673 --> 00:23:45,175
The system's monitoring it.

324
00:23:45,259 --> 00:23:46,927
I want it, too.

325
00:23:51,556 --> 00:23:53,058
I'll send you the link.

326
00:24:27,175 --> 00:24:29,094
Doug? This is Maurice.

327
00:24:29,177 --> 00:24:31,972
He'll be taking over for me.
I'm moving to Seattle.

328
00:24:32,055 --> 00:24:35,976
My sister's opening up her own PT center
and she wants me to be a partner.

329
00:24:36,059 --> 00:24:39,478
I'm moving all my clients
over to new folks.

330
00:24:39,562 --> 00:24:42,357
So I can help the transition.

331
00:24:42,441 --> 00:24:44,692
I'll be sad to see you go.

332
00:24:46,445 --> 00:24:48,322
I'll go get some bar floats.

333
00:24:48,405 --> 00:24:49,990
Back in a second.

334
00:24:52,075 --> 00:24:56,079
Look... I'm having people over
this Thursday.

335
00:24:56,163 --> 00:24:59,416
It's a going-away thing at my place.
You should come.

336
00:24:59,498 --> 00:25:01,751
- You ready?
- Yeah.

337
00:25:01,835 --> 00:25:03,795
I'll text you the details.

338
00:25:12,887 --> 00:25:16,016
I want to go after the big boys.
Not just Wall Street, but Walmart.

339
00:25:16,099 --> 00:25:19,227
I'd be careful with Walmart.
You'll lose a lot of friends in Congress.

340
00:25:19,311 --> 00:25:22,981
Let's force them to take sides.
That means Jackie Sharp, too.

341
00:25:23,064 --> 00:25:24,483
Introduce legislation.

342
00:25:24,565 --> 00:25:26,860
She either votes for it
or we hit her hard.

343
00:25:26,943 --> 00:25:30,197
Any corporation who has more than ten
percent of its employees on food stamps

344
00:25:30,280 --> 00:25:33,741
has to increase wages
until they're below ten percent.

345
00:25:35,285 --> 00:25:37,578
Who has the guts
to sponsor something like that?

346
00:25:47,588 --> 00:25:48,965
Doug?

347
00:25:50,384 --> 00:25:53,345
Yeah, I'll put a list together. You'll
have something by the end of the week.

348
00:25:53,428 --> 00:25:54,595
Okay. Talk to you then.

349
00:26:26,378 --> 00:26:29,423
- You made it.
- Yeah.

350
00:26:30,798 --> 00:26:33,176
- How long have you been here?
- Ten minutes.

351
00:26:33,260 --> 00:26:35,929
Come on.
We need to get people dancing.

352
00:26:36,012 --> 00:26:38,098
Actually, I was thinking
that I should go.

353
00:26:38,181 --> 00:26:40,683
I just came over to say goodbye.

354
00:26:40,767 --> 00:26:44,312
Uh-uh. No. You are not going anywhere.

355
00:26:44,396 --> 00:26:49,234
You don't have to dance,
but you can't leave.

356
00:27:04,374 --> 00:27:06,209
Last man standing.

357
00:27:08,920 --> 00:27:11,672
- You have recycling?
- Just leave 'em on the counter.

358
00:27:11,756 --> 00:27:13,800
I'll take care of it tomorrow.

359
00:27:18,888 --> 00:27:20,474
You really don't have to help.

360
00:27:20,557 --> 00:27:22,100
I don't mind.

361
00:27:24,685 --> 00:27:26,813
You're such a gentleman.

362
00:27:26,896 --> 00:27:28,940
I don't know about that.

363
00:27:29,023 --> 00:27:31,234
Oh, you're not a gentleman?

364
00:27:32,235 --> 00:27:35,614
Because... that could be interesting.

365
00:28:14,402 --> 00:28:17,280
I made you a cafÃ© au lait.

366
00:28:17,364 --> 00:28:19,240
Oh...

367
00:28:27,081 --> 00:28:28,583
How is it?

368
00:28:28,667 --> 00:28:30,627
- Need sugar?
- No.

369
00:28:30,709 --> 00:28:32,295
It's perfect.

370
00:28:34,506 --> 00:28:35,798
When are the movers coming by?

371
00:28:35,882 --> 00:28:38,926
Not for a couple hours.

372
00:28:39,010 --> 00:28:42,389
You need any help?
Packing the rest up?

373
00:28:42,472 --> 00:28:44,474
No. You just relax.

374
00:28:48,478 --> 00:28:51,022
You seemed a little sad last night.

375
00:28:52,315 --> 00:28:54,609
No, just tired.

376
00:28:54,693 --> 00:28:57,862
Was that it?
You were just tired?

377
00:29:03,326 --> 00:29:05,745
Someone I haven't heard from
in a long time.

378
00:29:07,205 --> 00:29:08,915
She reached out. It was--

379
00:29:08,998 --> 00:29:10,667
It was a little hard.

380
00:29:13,253 --> 00:29:16,172
Last night wasn't 'cause
you felt sorry for me, was it?

381
00:29:16,256 --> 00:29:18,299
No.

382
00:29:18,383 --> 00:29:22,387
Last night was because
I'm getting on a plane today,

383
00:29:22,470 --> 00:29:25,306
and I'll probably never see you again.

384
00:29:25,390 --> 00:29:27,141
Why not?

385
00:29:37,902 --> 00:29:40,154
You know it rains a lot in Seattle, right?

386
00:30:12,019 --> 00:30:14,689
Are you gonna come with me
to the memorial today?

387
00:30:15,898 --> 00:30:17,275
Do I need to be there?

388
00:30:17,358 --> 00:30:18,777
No.

389
00:30:21,446 --> 00:30:23,782
I'm buried right now.

390
00:30:23,864 --> 00:30:25,325
Fine.

391
00:31:02,487 --> 00:31:05,281
Why has Tom Yates been
hanging around so much?

392
00:31:05,365 --> 00:31:07,074
Is he writing a book on the president?

393
00:31:07,158 --> 00:31:09,452
We've all asked him and he won't say.

394
00:31:09,536 --> 00:31:11,579
Ballsy move if it's true.

395
00:31:11,663 --> 00:31:14,081
Yeah. I can't stand his writing.

396
00:31:15,291 --> 00:31:16,710
Are you an idiot?

397
00:31:16,793 --> 00:31:18,628
I'm an idiot for having an opinion?

398
00:31:18,712 --> 00:31:21,255
There's no opinions to be had.
His writing is gorgeous.

399
00:31:21,339 --> 00:31:23,591
Well, in my opinion, it isn't.

400
00:31:23,675 --> 00:31:25,635
Said the guy who can't write
a grocery list.

401
00:31:25,719 --> 00:31:28,346
- Shh, shh...
- Ready whenever you are, sir.

402
00:31:31,932 --> 00:31:35,687
Today marks the 80th Anniversary
of the Social Security Act.

403
00:31:35,770 --> 00:31:39,649
It has survived longer
than many of its beneficiaries.

404
00:31:39,733 --> 00:31:43,528
We should all be so lucky
to live as long as it has.

405
00:31:43,611 --> 00:31:48,032
But by the time the human body
has circled the sun 80 times,

406
00:31:48,115 --> 00:31:50,618
its youth and vigor are gone.

407
00:31:50,702 --> 00:31:53,913
Joints ache,
bones and muscles are weaker,

408
00:31:53,996 --> 00:31:57,709
the heart doesn't beat
with the same power it once did.

409
00:31:57,792 --> 00:32:00,837
All of us must face this truth eventually.

410
00:32:00,920 --> 00:32:04,090
And when we do,
we must hand the baton to the young.

411
00:32:04,173 --> 00:32:09,053
To those who have the strength
to carry on our work when we are gone.

412
00:32:09,136 --> 00:32:13,641
Here's another truth:
Social Security is dying.

413
00:32:13,725 --> 00:32:16,060
Now in its 80th year, it must give way

414
00:32:16,143 --> 00:32:20,231
to a new, younger,
stronger plan for the future.

415
00:32:20,314 --> 00:32:22,901
That plan is America Works.

416
00:32:22,983 --> 00:32:26,654
In Washington DC alone,
we've managed to reduce unemployment

417
00:32:26,738 --> 00:32:31,576
by over a third
and put 25,000 people to work.

418
00:32:31,659 --> 00:32:35,914
If we can accomplish so much
in so little time here in Washington,

419
00:32:35,996 --> 00:32:40,418
imagine what we could accomplish if
Congress funded America Works nationwide.

420
00:32:40,501 --> 00:32:42,879
We wouldn't be talking
about thousands of jobs.

421
00:32:42,962 --> 00:32:46,340
We'd be talking about millions.

422
00:32:46,424 --> 00:32:51,304
Later this afternoon, I will visit FDR's
memorial to pay my respects to the man

423
00:32:51,387 --> 00:32:55,015
who ushered in Social Security
80 years ago.

424
00:32:55,099 --> 00:32:58,812
We honor the dead for giving us
the world we inherited.

425
00:32:58,895 --> 00:33:05,443
However, we must recognize we are doomed
if we allow the dead to govern us.

426
00:33:05,526 --> 00:33:10,072
Thank you, and God bless
the United States of America.

427
00:33:10,156 --> 00:33:12,826
From NBC News in Washington,

428
00:33:12,909 --> 00:33:16,120
this is Meet the Press with Chuck Todd.

429
00:33:16,203 --> 00:33:18,498
Good morning and welcome
to Meet the Press.

430
00:33:18,581 --> 00:33:21,542
I have with me Congresswoman Huntley
and Congressman Greer.

431
00:33:21,626 --> 00:33:24,879
Congresswoman, let me start with you.
In the President's radio address today,

432
00:33:24,963 --> 00:33:29,216
he said the model here in Washington
is a model for the nation.

433
00:33:29,300 --> 00:33:31,302
- Do you agree?
- I do, Chuck.

434
00:33:31,385 --> 00:33:33,346
I was skeptical at first.

435
00:33:33,429 --> 00:33:35,807
Both my parents benefited
from Social Security.

436
00:33:35,890 --> 00:33:38,476
And I've always
counted on it for myself.

437
00:33:38,559 --> 00:33:41,896
But, when I think about my kids,
and my grandkids--

438
00:33:41,980 --> 00:33:44,148
Rebecca raises a good point,
one that we've been making

439
00:33:44,231 --> 00:33:45,775
in the Republican Party for decades.

440
00:33:45,859 --> 00:33:48,152
And yet, while you support America Works,

441
00:33:48,235 --> 00:33:50,363
most members of your party do not.

442
00:33:50,446 --> 00:33:52,782
Chuck, I've never been
a big fan of Frank Underwood.

443
00:33:52,866 --> 00:33:56,828
But the park near my house here
in Washington has never been cleaner.

444
00:33:56,911 --> 00:34:00,080
The dry cleaners I go to just hired
two new people this month.

445
00:34:00,164 --> 00:34:03,209
The daycare I drop my kids off at
doubled their staff

446
00:34:03,292 --> 00:34:05,628
so the children can get
more individual attention.

447
00:34:05,712 --> 00:34:08,840
The president may have overstepped
in taking FEMA money,

448
00:34:08,923 --> 00:34:12,886
but when something works, it works.
And America Works works.

449
00:35:18,701 --> 00:35:20,536
Hello.

450
00:37:26,913 --> 00:37:29,248
Promise the money.

451
00:37:29,331 --> 00:37:33,627
Whatever you need to turn him around.
I'll approve the USAID funds.

452
00:37:35,755 --> 00:37:38,007
What made you change your mind?

453
00:37:40,551 --> 00:37:44,013
Today... at the memorial.

454
00:37:46,057 --> 00:37:48,935
You know what struck me the most?

455
00:37:52,105 --> 00:37:53,898
Eleanor.

456
00:37:55,691 --> 00:37:58,069
She was off by herself.

457
00:37:58,152 --> 00:37:59,946
Alone.

458
00:38:01,321 --> 00:38:03,950
And so was Franklin. He was alone.

459
00:38:07,036 --> 00:38:09,622
And there was a wall between them.

460
00:38:13,751 --> 00:38:15,586
The monks.

461
00:38:15,669 --> 00:38:19,048
They've been here for weeks.
We haven't even discussed them once.

462
00:38:20,716 --> 00:38:22,676
It's beautiful, isn't it?
What they're doing?

463
00:38:22,760 --> 00:38:24,303
It is.

464
00:38:29,433 --> 00:38:32,311
Francis, I watched them
for over an hour today.

465
00:38:32,394 --> 00:38:36,649
And all I was thinking was, why aren't
you and I sharing this together?

466
00:38:46,700 --> 00:38:48,911
We have to do something, Claire.

467
00:38:51,038 --> 00:38:52,539
I know.

468
00:38:56,335 --> 00:38:57,962
What are you thinking?

469
00:38:58,045 --> 00:39:01,715
My natural color.
Like when I first met Francis.

470
00:39:02,549 --> 00:39:05,594
- This color?
- Yes. Exactly.

471
00:39:05,678 --> 00:39:07,221
Okay. Have a seat.

472
00:39:26,282 --> 00:39:27,867
I want to take up the sleeves a touch.

473
00:39:27,950 --> 00:39:30,410
Oh, I think they're perfect.
Thank you.

474
00:39:35,582 --> 00:39:38,294
- What do you think?
- Beautiful.

475
00:40:00,607 --> 00:40:05,029
We have gathered today to renew
the vows between Francis J. Underwood

476
00:40:05,112 --> 00:40:08,615
and Claire Hale Underwood.

477
00:40:12,661 --> 00:40:15,081
It was here, in this church,

478
00:40:15,164 --> 00:40:18,751
28 years ago, before God,

479
00:40:18,834 --> 00:40:22,213
that you two first committed
yourselves to one another.

480
00:40:28,928 --> 00:40:32,348
May this renewed commitment
deepen your love for each other,

481
00:40:32,431 --> 00:40:34,934
and strengthen your eternal bond.

482
00:41:17,268 --> 00:41:20,062
Claire's father bought us this house.

483
00:41:20,146 --> 00:41:23,649
I wanted to pay for it myself.
That's always bothered me.

484
00:41:23,732 --> 00:41:26,568
You weren't bothered to let him pay
for your first campaign?

485
00:41:26,652 --> 00:41:30,572
Well, that's politics. It's different.
You take money wherever you can get it.

486
00:41:30,656 --> 00:41:32,825
No, this was our first home.

487
00:41:33,867 --> 00:41:36,495
- Was it a happy home?
- Oh, please.

488
00:41:38,331 --> 00:41:41,250
I thought you brought me here because
we were gonna cut through the bullshit.

489
00:41:41,334 --> 00:41:43,252
This book is supposed to be
about America Works.

490
00:41:43,336 --> 00:41:45,629
There is no book
without you at the center of it.

491
00:41:47,256 --> 00:41:49,633
Do you trust me? Or don't you?

492
00:41:49,716 --> 00:41:51,760
Because if you don't,
get someone else to write it.

493
00:41:51,844 --> 00:41:52,845
Or write it yourself.

494
00:41:52,928 --> 00:41:56,307
You don't know what it's like to go
through life looking over your shoulder.

495
00:41:56,390 --> 00:41:58,725
Having secrets no one would understand.

496
00:41:58,809 --> 00:42:00,686
I didn't write my first book.

497
00:42:02,521 --> 00:42:04,106
My friend.

498
00:42:05,858 --> 00:42:09,236
- The one who died.
- He wrote it?

499
00:42:09,320 --> 00:42:12,114
The first half.
He didn't show it to anyone except me.

500
00:42:12,198 --> 00:42:14,616
In the hospital, he asked me destroy it.

501
00:42:14,700 --> 00:42:16,494
I told him I would.

502
00:42:19,913 --> 00:42:21,915
It was too good.

503
00:42:21,999 --> 00:42:24,210
It needed to be finished.
So I finished it.

504
00:42:24,293 --> 00:42:29,089
- And took all the credit.
- Oh, yeah. It's my part, the ending.

505
00:42:29,173 --> 00:42:30,716
That's what people remember.

506
00:42:31,925 --> 00:42:33,677
But the book...

507
00:42:35,679 --> 00:42:37,348
My entire career...

508
00:42:39,725 --> 00:42:41,310
It's all based on a lie.

509
00:42:41,394 --> 00:42:44,146
You don't have a monopoly on secrets.

510
00:42:57,535 --> 00:42:59,578
There's tulips buried under here.

511
00:43:01,414 --> 00:43:03,332
Claire planted them.

512
00:43:07,753 --> 00:43:09,505
I've always...

513
00:43:11,882 --> 00:43:13,759
from day one...

514
00:43:16,178 --> 00:43:19,139
been ashamed she said yes
when I asked her to marry me.

515
00:43:19,223 --> 00:43:20,807
Why?

516
00:43:23,185 --> 00:43:25,229
I didn't think I deserved her.

517
00:43:28,023 --> 00:43:31,485
I can tell you this, though, there would
have been no White House without Claire.

518
00:43:31,569 --> 00:43:34,113
I was half the man before I met her.

519
00:43:34,196 --> 00:43:36,823
But still, I've been selfish...

520
00:43:38,367 --> 00:43:40,702
feeding off her the way I have.

521
00:43:40,786 --> 00:43:42,746
She knew what she was getting into.

522
00:43:43,997 --> 00:43:48,627
Probably. She knows me
better than I know myself.

523
00:43:49,545 --> 00:43:52,256
Sir? We're scheduled to fly out at 6:15.

524
00:43:52,339 --> 00:43:54,300
Should probably leave
in the next few minutes.

525
00:43:54,383 --> 00:43:56,302
Thank you, Meechum.

526
00:44:01,014 --> 00:44:02,766
Scribble away.

527
00:44:12,485 --> 00:44:15,654
So, what'd he tell you
in front of the house?

528
00:44:15,737 --> 00:44:17,323
Mm...

529
00:44:17,406 --> 00:44:18,949
Nothing much.

530
00:44:19,032 --> 00:44:21,034
Well, it looked intense,
whatever it was.

531
00:44:21,118 --> 00:44:25,205
See? This is why I don't ride in the van.

532
00:44:25,289 --> 00:44:27,207
You did this time.

533
00:44:29,960 --> 00:44:32,171
Sometimes you just need
to leave someone alone.

534
00:44:32,254 --> 00:44:35,424
All right, I got the hint.

535
00:44:35,508 --> 00:44:39,470
I meant him. Not me.

536
00:45:05,496 --> 00:45:07,373
Where are they?

537
00:45:07,456 --> 00:45:10,250
- Who?
- The monks.

538
00:45:10,334 --> 00:45:12,752
Oh, they finished earlier today, sir.

539
00:45:13,711 --> 00:45:15,464
So it's gone?

540
00:45:15,548 --> 00:45:17,841
I believe so.

541
00:45:17,924 --> 00:45:20,052
I didn't get a chance to see it.

542
00:45:20,135 --> 00:45:21,970
I'm sure they took a photo.

543
00:45:24,056 --> 00:45:26,642
Will you ask someone to get me a copy?

544
00:45:26,724 --> 00:45:28,726
Right away, sir.

545
00:46:31,665 --> 00:46:33,083
Thank you.

546
00:46:38,213 --> 00:46:41,133
Claire.
I almost didn't recognize you.

547
00:46:41,216 --> 00:46:43,843
Yes,
I decided it was time for a change.

548
00:46:43,927 --> 00:46:45,763
It's very fetching.

549
00:46:45,845 --> 00:46:47,973
I hope you don't mind me
crashing your party.

550
00:46:48,056 --> 00:46:51,226
Oh, of course not.
My staff said you'd be out of town.

551
00:46:51,310 --> 00:46:54,980
Would you mind if I borrowed
Ambassador Caspi for a moment?

552
00:46:55,063 --> 00:46:56,064
Of course.

553
00:46:59,025 --> 00:47:02,571
- You've been avoiding me for three weeks.
- I had a trip to Jerusalem.

554
00:47:04,239 --> 00:47:06,283
You promised Zimbabwe 35 million

555
00:47:06,366 --> 00:47:09,077
so they'd introduce
the poison pill amendment.

556
00:47:09,161 --> 00:47:11,455
- For purely humanitarian reasons.
- No.

557
00:47:11,538 --> 00:47:15,250
This is the first time
you've ever sent aid to Zimbabwe.

558
00:47:15,334 --> 00:47:18,003
Don't draw connections that don't exist.

559
00:47:18,086 --> 00:47:21,465
We would never try
to sabotage the resolution.

560
00:47:21,548 --> 00:47:25,302
- The United States is our ally.
- That's right, we are.

561
00:47:25,385 --> 00:47:28,972
- So act like it.
- Excuse me?

562
00:47:29,055 --> 00:47:33,352
My husband formally approved our own
humanitarian package for eighty million.

563
00:47:33,435 --> 00:47:38,064
Zimbabwe will be withdrawing
the amendment tomorrow.

564
00:47:38,148 --> 00:47:40,233
And when the resolution goes to a vote,

565
00:47:40,317 --> 00:47:43,737
I expect Israel to support it
like the loyal ally she is.

566
00:47:43,821 --> 00:47:45,781
Not lie to us.

567
00:47:45,863 --> 00:47:48,116
That's not the way to solicit our support.

568
00:47:48,200 --> 00:47:51,537
I'm not soliciting. I'm demanding.

569
00:47:51,620 --> 00:47:54,289
I feel sorry for you, Claire.

570
00:47:54,373 --> 00:47:57,543
Your husband sends you to talk tough.

571
00:47:57,626 --> 00:48:00,462
But as soon as things go wrong
in the Jordan Valley,

572
00:48:00,546 --> 00:48:03,382
he'll turn his back and leave Israel
to clean up the mess.

573
00:48:03,465 --> 00:48:04,924
He doesn't have the muscle.

574
00:48:05,008 --> 00:48:07,093
He can't even get Congress
to work with him.

575
00:48:07,177 --> 00:48:09,388
Or back you up after you call out Petrov.

576
00:48:09,471 --> 00:48:12,516
He turned his back on you
just like he will on us.

577
00:48:14,892 --> 00:48:19,064
My husband is the bravest
and most resolute man I know.

578
00:48:19,147 --> 00:48:20,566
He will succeed in this plan.

579
00:48:20,649 --> 00:48:22,359
Brave?

580
00:48:22,442 --> 00:48:24,277
I served in Jordan Valley.

581
00:48:24,361 --> 00:48:26,988
As did the President
and the Foreign Minister. Has he?

582
00:48:28,574 --> 00:48:32,411
You held a gun and somebody
told you where to stand.

583
00:48:32,494 --> 00:48:37,332
Don't confuse that with the burden
the Commander in Chief faces.

584
00:48:37,416 --> 00:48:39,084
Francis has given the order to kill.

585
00:48:39,167 --> 00:48:41,628
He's buried soldiers
he's put into harm's way.

586
00:48:41,712 --> 00:48:44,548
And every day,
he wakes up bearing responsibilities

587
00:48:44,631 --> 00:48:46,717
you can't possibly imagine.

588
00:48:46,800 --> 00:48:49,386
They would crush you
if they fell on your shoulders.

589
00:48:49,469 --> 00:48:51,555
So you talk to your superiors.

590
00:48:52,514 --> 00:48:55,141
And when the amendment
is withdrawn tomorrow,

591
00:48:55,225 --> 00:48:59,062
you will commit
to supporting the resolution.

592
00:49:42,773 --> 00:49:44,107
Oh...

593
